text.tspan: Optional battery protection C15, R26, R27, Q10, Q11, Q12
for the use of unprotected cells. Can be by-passed with jumper J1
<15µA stand-by current / up to 4 years stand-by time with a 500mAh LiPo - or 1 year stand-by, used 10-20 times per day
4 LED indicators (Charging, charging finished, button pressed, MCU controlled)
Buffered buttons and no noticeable delay when waking up from deep sleep using quick connect
Charging between 6 and 42°C PCB temp. (45-80% VCC @ TEMP Pin) with R16/100K NTC
Do not leave TEMP floating, the PCB traces can cause capacitively coupling, R15=5M/R16=2.4M can be used

g.text: Q2 discharges the store and hold capacitors for the switches when the MCU is running

text.tspan: Rev1.2 - Fixed SW1-4, removed duplicate net, changed R21 to 1K, increased C9 to 100nF, added D10-D12 and pulldowns

g.text: Note: GPIO12, 13 and 14 are pulled HIGH during boot and required a diode and pulldown resistor
Note: While charging, the MCU is powered via USB as well and can monitor the progress
Note: The ADC readings are not stable with WiFi active
